On January 10, 2018, the President signed several laws, including H.R. 381, which designates a mountain in the Sierra National Forest in California as Sky Point. H.R. 699, the Mount Hood Cooper Spur Land Exchange Clarification Act, amends current law relating to land exchanges in the Mt. Hood Wilderness in Oregon. H.R. 863 amends current law relating to the Coltsville National Historical Park. H.R. 2142, the INTERDICT Act, requires U.S. Customs and Border Protection to increase the number of chemical screening devices used to detect illegally imported narcotics, such as fentanyl, and dedicate personnel to interpret data collected by such devices. H.R. 2228, the Law Enforcement Mental Health and Wellness Act, requires the Justice Department to submit a report to Congress on mental health services for law enforcement agencies and allows grant funds to be used for mental health and wellness pilot programs. Lastly, H.R. 2331, the Connected Government Act, requires new or updated Federal websites for public use to be mobile friendly.